                            <comment id="14492091" author="struberg" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 09:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Thomas!&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the report!&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve tested a few of my customers webapps without any problems. But I also do not use CDI Conversations &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
If you can extract a smallish example then we might improve the Conversation support even more and ship a fix in a 1.5.1 release in a few weeks?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492107" author="tandraschko" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 09:11:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Mark,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is also DON&apos;T use conversations but this occurs on every request as a transient conversation is started for each request &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will provide a sample app the next hours.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492119" author="tandraschko" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 09:24:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;just start via mvn clean package jetty:run and open /index.xhtml via the browser.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492120" author="romain.manni-bucau" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2015 09:24:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it can help, in TomEE we expect a request: org.apache.openejb.cdi.CdiAppContextsService#initConversationContext which is what makes sense IMO since the conversation context should be retrieved from the request or created for transient conversations.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14496642" author="struberg" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2015 18:24:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve fixed the Exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Conversation handling is still a big buggy. But I think this is not that important for now as most people don&apos;t use CDI conversations but CODI or DeltaSpike for it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should fix this by also cleaning up our session handling. I&apos;ll open another ticket for this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14501957" author="struberg" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2015 14:53:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue got shipped with OpenWebBeans-1.5.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
